# =============================================================================
# Ham dashboard — copy to `.env.local` (or set in your host’s env UI).
# Model / OpenRouter keys live on the FastAPI backend (repo root `.env`), not here.
# Hermes-on-GCE / gateway env (`HERMES_GATEWAY_*`) is server-side only — see repo root
# `.env.example` and `docs/DEPLOY_CLOUD_RUN.md` (browser never calls Hermes).
# =============================================================================

# --- Ham API (chat, context, workspace APIs) ---
#
# Local development
#   Leave VITE_HAM_API_BASE unset. The app calls same-origin `/api/*`; Vite proxies
#   to FastAPI (see `vite.config.ts`).
#
# Production (Vercel, static host, etc.)
#   Set VITE_HAM_API_BASE to your deployed Ham API origin — no path, no trailing slash,
#   and no /api suffix (the app appends /api/... itself).
#   Set it for Production and Preview, then redeploy (Vite embeds VITE_* at build time).
#
# VITE_HAM_API_BASE=https://your-ham-api-xxxxx.run.app
# Wrong: https://your-ham-api.run.app/api

# Optional — Clerk publishable key (dashboard). When set, App wraps ClerkProvider and Chat sends the session JWT
# as Authorization; operator confirm tokens use X-Ham-Operator-Authorization. Requires API env HAM_CLERK_REQUIRE_AUTH
# + CLERK_JWT_ISSUER when you want server-side enforcement.
# VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...

# Optional — namespaced Hermes Workspace UI lift (see docs/WHOLE_HERMES_WORKSPACE_LIFT_PLAN.md).
# When true, `/chat` redirects to `/workspace/chat` so the primary URL shows the Hermes shell.
# Set this in Vercel (Production + Preview) and redeploy; it is baked in at build time.
# VITE_ENABLE_HERMES_WORKSPACE=true

# Optional — dev / `vite preview` only: where Vite forwards same-origin `/api/*` (default
# http://127.0.0.1:8000 in `vite.config.ts`). Set this to the local HAM FastAPI port that actually
# serves the routes you need (e.g. GET /api/workspace/files, /api/chat/...). If another app owns
# :8000 or your uvicorn is on :8001, you MUST set the matching URL here or Workspace Files will
# show "Runtime bridge pending" and list XHRs may 404 — restart Vite after changing. Do not commit
# `.env.local` (gitignored); use this file as the template only.
# VITE_HAM_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8000
# VITE_HAM_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8001

# =============================================================================
# Optional — not used by the current Ham UI (no imports in `src/`).
# Kept because `vite.config.ts` still injects `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY` for
# `@google/genai` if you add browser-side Gemini later.
# =============================================================================

# Google AI Studio / Gemini API key (only if you wire client-side calls yourself).
# GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Public site URL — not referenced by this frontend today; useful if you add OAuth
# or absolute callback URLs later.
# APP_URL=https://your-dashboard.example.com
